The paper proposes a new optimization objective for value-based deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The addition of a model-learning component and the use of a transcoder network also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The experiments are conducted on Atari games, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning also suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
